anwhile, preheat oven to 150°C and line 2 large baking trays with baking paper."},{"content":"Slice loaf thinly (2-3 mm) using a sharp knife and place slices on prepared baking trays. Bake for 10 minutes (150°C) then turn slices over and bake for a further 10 minutes (150°C) until golden. Transfer slices to a wire rack to cool and harden."},{"content":"Serve or store in an airtight container for up to 5 days."}],"hintsAndTricks":["When testing the baked loaf with a skewer, you may pierce a piece of fruit so it doesn't matter if not completely clean.","Bake in 2 smaller tins, for smaller slices.","Wrap resulting slices in cling film, for a softer, chewier result."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","6h 15m","30 slices"]}